datagenerator.fields
Interface Field

All Superinterfaces:
java.io.Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
AutoIncField, CharStringField, CustomField, CustomWieghtField, LocationField, NameGenderField, NumberDoubleField, NumberIntField
public interface Field
extends java.io.Serializable

Field Classes are designed to work similar to the java.util.Random Class. Once prepared and configured the Field has a nextField method which produces the one record of the desired random data. The Field should also have a configure method who's parameters take in the different configuration options chosen by the user.

Author:
Patrick McMorran

nextField

java.lang.String nextField()
This method is similar to the nextInt method of the random class, in that it returns a string containing the randomly generated field(s) that Field Introduced.

Returns:
This method returns a string containing the randomly generated data. If the Field Generates multiple columns, they will be comma spaced.
